From: Peter Jones <pjones@redhat.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2015 11:35:54 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] Always use upper case for Boot#### names.

UEFI requires upper case names...

Signed-off-by: Peter Jones <pjones@redhat.com>
---
 linux/libfwup.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/linux/libfwup.c b/linux/libfwup.c
index d0cac8d..4a8bd2a 100644
--- a/linux/libfwup.c
+++ b/linux/libfwup.c
@@ -687,7 +687,7 @@ do_next:
 		if (boot_next >= 0x10000)
 			goto out;
 
-		sprintf(boot_next_name, "Boot%04x", boot_next);
+		sprintf(boot_next_name, "Boot%04X", boot_next);
 		rc = efi_set_variable(*guid, boot_next_name, opt, opt_size,
 				      EFI_VARIABLE_NON_VOLATILE |
 				      EFI_VARIABLE_BOOTSERVICE_ACCESS |
